title: Delphi FG0931 Fuel Module
features: Delphi brings 80 + years of OE Heritage into each Delphi assembly, ensuring quality and fitment for each Delphi part
Internal springs increase durability by preventing tube chaffing
Strainer is internal to module - providing better protection to the strainer element and improved filtering
Rigorous OE-testing ensures the pump can withstand extreme temperatures
Always be sure to check and clean fuel tank to avoid unnecessary returns
Durability tested up to 150,000 miles and in more than 20% ethanol for superior reliability
Patented Gen IV turbine pump provides better pumping with less energy use and withstands today’s harsh alcohol fuel blends
description: Delphi's fuel pump module assemblies for GM, Toyota and Honda applications are designed with the benefit of more than 100 years of OE heritage and cover over 4 million North American vehicles on the road today. All of these newly released fuel pump module assemblies feature Delphi’s Gen IV turbine pump, which utilizes their latest OE fuel pump technologies and materials.
